  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA) in the United States\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations in many countries\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) protocols\n\n3. Key Prevention Strategies\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- International information sharing\n- Substantial financial penalties for non-compliance\n\n4. Common Regulatory Requirements\n- Mandatory identification verification\n- Record-keeping\n- Reporting large cash transactions\n- Enhanced scrutiny of high-risk sectors\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial investigations\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Regulatory sanctions\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different financial sectors and jurisdictions.",
